  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Totem is offered on a half board basis, breakfast and evening meals are included within the package price.</p>
<p>Each day fuel up for a day on the slopes, enjoy an extensive continental breakfast buffet with additional hot options served between 7-10am (times subject to change).</p>
<p>Each night, between 7 and 9:30pm, dinner is served in the spacious restaurant. You can choose from an extensive buffet including a variety of different themed stations. </p>
<p>Christmas and New Year gala dinners are included. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>With the convenience of doorstep skiing and finished to a very high standard the Hotel Totem combines modern and vintage furniture and fabrics with a distinctive North American feel. A relaxing spa area is the perfect end to a day on the slopes, with two saunas, a relaxation room and an outdoor whirlpool overlooking the mountains.  </p>
<h2>Ski and explore Flaine</h2>
<p>With an idylic location in <a data-udi="umb://document/5f7cf8fdbd684bd5bba7644eede878ac" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5f7cf8fdbd684bd5bba7644eede878ac}" title="Flaine">Flaine</a>, you can be on the slopes in no time. The slopes and ski lifts are less than 100 metres away, making it easy and convenient to get onto the Grand Massif ski area each day.</p>
<p>The architecture and design of Flaine makes it more like an open-air modern art museum than a traditional ski resort. The Hotel Totem had been designed in keeping of the rest of the resort architecture, the interior of the hotel combines exposed concrete with vintage furniture and fabrics - <span>numerous urban references are matched to the mountain landscape. </span><span>As well as the distinct architecture, you can also find the works of Pablo Picasso, Jean Dubuffet and Victor Vasarely dotted around the resort. </span></p>
<h2>Unwind and relax</h2>
<p>There is nowhere better to be than in the hotels own wellness area, marvel at the mountains from the outdoor whirlpool or sooth your muscles in the sauna. Treat yourself to a massage or a treatment for a moment of rejuvenation, spa treatments are available to book locally for a little extra cost. There is also a fitness room with a variety of equipment available, so you can train for your next ski adventure.</p>
<p>After a day of exploring the mountain, enjoy a drink at the hotel bar serving a range of local beers, French wines and cocktails inspired by the surrounding area. The terrace is a great place to soak up some winter sun, with wonderful views of the slopes and surrounding mountain peaks.</p>
<p>Each evening you have a large choice of dishes, the kitchen<span> team prepare a buffet changing each evening, using local, fresh and seasonal products. There is often </span>regional dishes such as tartiflette and fondue, as well as pizza, hearty soup, and kids' specials. </p>]]></description>
